  "prompt": "Which is the best android phone above 35000?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, there are several excellent Android smartphones available in India above \u20b935,000. The \"best\" phone depends on your specific needs, such as camera quality, performance, display, battery life, or gaming capabilities. Here are some of the top contenders:\n\n---\n\n### **Best Android Phones Above \u20b935,000**\n1. **Samsung Galaxy S21 FE 5G**  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b935,000\u201340,000  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.4-inch AMOLED 120Hz display  \n     - Snapdragon 888 / Exynos 2100 (depending on region)  \n     - Triple rear cameras (12MP + 12MP + 8MP)  \n     - 4,500mAh battery with 25W fast charging  \n     - Sleek design and IP68 water resistance  \n\n2. **OnePlus 11R 5G**  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b939,999  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.74-inch Fluid AMOLED 120Hz display  \n     - Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 processor  \n     - 50MP main camera with Sony IMX890 sensor  \n     - 5,000mAh battery with 100W fast charging  \n     - Excellent performance for gaming and multitasking  \n\n3. **Nothing Phone (2)**  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b944,999  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.7-inch LTPO OLED 120Hz display  \n     - Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 processor  \n     - Dual 50MP cameras (Sony IMX890 + JN1)  \n     - 4,700mAh battery with 45W fast charging  \n     - Unique Glyph Interface and premium design  \n\n4. **Google Pixel 7**  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b945,000  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.3-inch AMOLED 90Hz display  \n     - Google Tensor G2 processor  \n     - Dual 50MP + 12MP cameras (excellent for photography)  \n     - 4,355mAh battery with 20W fast charging  \n     - Pure Android experience with long-term software updates  \n\n5. **iQOO 9 Pro 5G**  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b945,000\u201350,000  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.78-inch AMOLED 120Hz LTPO display  \n     - Snapdragon 8 Gen 1 processor  \n     - Triple rear cameras (50MP + 50MP + 16MP)  \n     - 4,700mAh battery with 120W fast charging  \n     - Great for gaming and multimedia  \n\n6. **Samsung Galaxy A54 5G**  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b938,999  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.4-inch Super AMOLED 120Hz display  \n     - Exynos 1380 processor  \n     - Triple 50MP rear cameras  \n     - 5,000mAh battery with 25W fast charging  \n     - IP67 water resistance  \n\n---\n\n### **Factors to Consider**\n- **Performance**: For gaming and heavy multitasking, go for phones like the OnePlus 11R, iQOO 9 Pro, or Nothing Phone (2).  \n- **Camera**: Google Pixel 7 and Samsung Galaxy S21 FE are excellent for photography.  \n- **Software**: Pixel 7 offers the cleanest Android experience with timely updates.  \n- **Battery & Charging**: iQOO 9 Pro and OnePlus 11R excel in fast charging.  \n- **Brand Preference**: Choose Samsung for reliability, OnePlus/Nothing for a premium feel, or Pixel for software and camera.  \n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like help narrowing down based on specific requirements!",
